{"/service/ndnp/az/batch_az_iotite_ver01/data/sn84020064/00529040106/1930110101/0003.xml":{"full_text":"DOUGLAS, ARIZONA\nVoters Recognize Bunk of U<m<li<lale\nHunt's Slogan. Which Is Proving Real\nBoomerang As Flection Approaches\nPHOENIX, Oct. 31.\u2014'The \"Back\nto prosperity campaign vehicle ol\nformer Governor Geo. W. P. Hutu\nis limping along the Una Meg of\nI*e 1930 Arizona gubernatorial race\nwith a flat tire while the Phillips\nbandwagon is purring ahead with\nIncreased vigor as the Nov. 4 finish\nnears, according to a statement la\nsued today by republican state cen\ntral committee headquarters.\nContending that the campaign\nrlogan of the democratic nominee\nla proving a boomerang among vot\nin all sections of the state, the\ncommittee declared that \u201cthe people\nof Arteorui are well aware of the\nfhet that Mr. Hunt will have no\nmore to do with the return of\nprosperity than he will have with\nthe state of wcather-rthc pro&per\ncatch phrase has proved to be\nOfily a bubble which has bursted.\u201d\n\u201cMr. Hunt's proposal for the end\ning of depression,\u201d continued the\nstatement, \"embrAoes a road build\ning program to be carried out by\nthe state highway commission.\n\u201cThis commission Is still Hunt\ncontrolled. appointees of the former\ngovernor dominating the commis\nsion end directing its activities.\nMr Phillips has never had any\ncontrol over this commission.\n\"If Mr. Hunt Is as sincere in\nhelping the state out of chaos as\nhe claims to be, why doesn't he\npall on bis appointees for such a\n-program now when it is needed in\nstead of waiting until after elec\ntion? Why didn\u2019t he do it six\nTMonths ago. if, as he says, he has\nIke welfare of Arizona at his heart,\n\u2018the commission can do as much\nnow and iould have done as much\nfitx months or more ago toward\nrelieving depression as it will be\nAble to do after Jan. 1. Mr. Hunt\nknow., that, but he expects the\npeople to believe that by sonic\n(hystericus process his election on\nNov. 4 will, like Aladdin's lamp,\nprovide the open sesame to the\nsolution of all ills and problems.\u201d\ni Declaring that If he expects to\nApply his \"back to prosperity\u201d rem\nedy fhrougn large appropriations\nfrom tlie state legislature for a\nroad-building program, the com-\nmittee asserted that \u201cMr. Hunt\nhas never been able to get along\nwith the legislature\u2014Oovcrnor Phil\nlips. a republican, has worked in\nmore harmony with a democratic\nlegislature during his only term in\noffice than has the former gover-\nnor in his last three terms in the\ngubernatorial chair.\u201d\n\u201cThe highway commission at this 1\nIPIGGLV WIGGLY\nj HELPS THOSE WHO HELP ;THEMSEU\u00abW\nPeaches\nDel Monte, Sliced, No. 2 Vi\u00bb 40c\nMustard\nFrench 1 A\nPrepared lTv\n\u00abJello\nAll Flavors\u2014 OO\n3 pkgs. for uIAb\nOats\n3-Minute\nLarge China ODC\nCake Flour\nRegular Swansdown, QC\nWith Cake Plate \u00abWC\nMince Meat\nMon-Such, 1 [V\n10-oz. pkg It/C\nPotatoes\n10 lbs., Idaho, OO\nRussett \u00abOC\nBeans\nGreen, Fresh, OT\n2 lbs. for \u00a3DC\nBoiling Beef\nFresh and Tender, t\nPer pound\nPork Roast\nUan 24c\nper pound\nHOMJC-OWNED AND HOME OPERATED\ni lime, however.\" continued Ihr state\nment, \u2018i.i not concerned in \u2018back to\nprospsrity.* unless the t 'rm is made\nto apply to the prosperous few\nwho will benefit by the election of\nMr. Hunt. As on primary election\nday last September, the hundreds\n>f employes of the highway de\npartment will be given the day off\nfor concentrated efforts in behalf\nof Mr. Hunt at the polls. Every\none employed in any work is al\nlowed two hours off in which to\ni cart their vote, but employes of the\nHunt-dominated highway depart\nment are given the full day off the\njob to campaign for their candi\ndatSt\u2014and they draw. Just the same,\ni thi! day's pay. which comes out ol\nI the taxpayers' pecketbookr.\n\u201cIn all fairness to Mr. Cane,\nchief engineer of the highway de\npartment. it should be mentioned\nthat he strongly opposed the cf\nfoits of the cqpimission to permit\nhighway employes to take part in\nrucli an infamous plan on primary\nI election day last September. But\nagainst his wishes in the matter,\n!be was forced to abide by the\nmandate of the Hunt-controlled\nhighway commission.\"\nThe committee appealed to the\nfairness of the voters of Arizona\nto \u201cgive Mr. Phillips a chance to\nintroduce in the highway commis\nsion the same economy he has ap\nplied to state institutions under his\ncontrol by re-electing him and giv\ning him an opportunity to select a\ncommission of his own appointees\nand accountable to him for their\nactions..\u201d\n\u2018\u2018The now famous force account\nsystem used in the building of the\nroads under Mr. Hunt\u2019s previous\nadministration, resulting in flag\nrant extravagance and waste of the\npeople\u2019s money should convince the\npeople of Arizona that a change is\nneeded in the supervision of their\nhighway construction program\u201dthe\nstatement continued.\n\u2018The legislative report, rendered\nby a democratic committee, con\ncerning tin? force account system\ngives the facts in the case without\nembellishment. They speak for\nthemselves.\n\u201cQuoting from the report of the\ncommittee, it is shown that the\nbuilding of four miles of Apache\ntrail cost the state $184,174 under\nthe force account system, while the\nrams work would have b.xn car\nried out for $71,000 by contract.\nThe Water Users association, after\nmaking a study of the project,\nMeal\nRoman\nA Cereal\nPumpkin\nEmpson\u2019s 1T\nNo. 2/i Tin 13C\nMalted Milk\nThompson\u2019sChocolatc\n1-pound OQ\ntin\nOUR PRODUCE\nCabbage\nFirm and Green O\nper lb\nCelery\nBleached, Crisp 1 O\nper hunch l\u00a3v\nOUR MARKET\nSausage\nFresh Pork,\nper lb ZUC\nDOUGUAS DAILY n.SPATCH, SATURDAY MORNING. NOVEMBER 1. 1930.\nPolice Seize \u201cBugs\u201d Moran\nHfl f 'HLi ifiJ\nl.?v v IS HSU\nAt*-*\nB jilf- a \\<T uv r\nC.iorgc \u201cltugV >1\u00ab ran, notorious head of Uie North Side gang of\nChicago, and Al Cnponr\u2019s chief rival, is shown here as he was ar\ntaigneii in the Waukegan i 111.1 (ov-rtroom on chorees of vagrancy\nand carrying a gun. Moran had hern sought for questioning in con\nnection with the murder of Jake langle, iiicajo reporter.\nmade this estimate.\n\u201cFourteen miles of the Solomon\nvillc road, the report continues,\ncost the state S2IOOOO under the\nforce account system, while by con\ntract the project could have been\ncompleted for $114,000, a loss of\n$95,000 to the state.\n\u201cFederal aid project 69 rost the\nstate $220,000 and could have been\ndone for $125,000. another loss of\n$95X4)0 to the state. Is this econ\nomy and does it indicate any rem\nedy fer the relief of depression?\nMenus (or ihe Family I\n\nnr sifter maky\nTil Writer\nMANY pcHhini like to cure a\nham, shoulder and several\npieces of bacon themselves. It'a\nreally very little trouble to euro\nthe meat, and home-cured ham Js\nlike a vegetable from \u201cour own\nrarden.\u201d\nLard, too, can be tried out in\none's own kitchen to good advan\ntage. If economy is an important\nfactor the housewife will find that\nthese tasks are well w\u2019orth her\nwhile.\nOf course the smoking can\u2019t be\naccomplished at home, but as most\nbutchers have tiieir own arrange\nments for smoking meats they are\nwilling to look after this part of\nthe curing for their customers.\nThere are two common methods\nof curing pork. \u201cSugar cured\u201d\nmeats are usually considered the\ntiiH'-u. although those cured in a\nbrine are preferred by some peo\nple.\nTo Sugar Cure Pork\nTwo and one-half pounds salt,\n2 I*2 ounces pepper, I*2 ounce\nsalt petre, 1 cup molasses. 50\npounds pork.\nHub about 1 tablespoon table\nsalt around the bone of bam or\nshoulder. Hub well with molasses.\nMix salt, pepper and salt petre\nthoroughly and rub well into the\nmeat. Use about one-third of the\nmixture and let stand three days.\nRub two more times at three\nday intervals, making three rub\nbings in all. Let stand in a cool,\ndry place for from four to six\nwcek3. Then have smoked.\n*4 O\nTo Cure with Drino\nFirst rub each ham or shoulder\nwith 1 tablespoon powdered salt\npetre. Hub around the bone with\nt- ispoon peppaf. Mix 1 1-2\npounds brown sugar with 2 cups\n\u2022alt and rub meat well with this,\nl'bis quality Is enough for nft>*\npounds of meat. Put a layer of\nsalt in the bottom of a tub. Put\nn meat, skin side down. Sprin\nkle with salt and add more meat.\nLet stand In this salt for eight\nlays. Take out. wipe off all the\njalt and wash the tub. Combine\nDaily Menu\nBREAKFAST\u2014Baked ap\nples, cereal, cream, baked\nhush, whole wheat muffins,\nmilk, coffee.\nLUNCHEON Cream of\nparsnip soup, croutons, stuff\ned green peppers, toasted muf\nfins, baked custard, grape\njuice.\nDINNER \u2014Roast loin of\npork, candied sweet potatoes,\ncreamed corn, cabbage and\ncelery salad, apple pudding,\nmilk, coffee.\ni ounces salt petrc, 8 cup;; raolas\nica, 2 cups salt and 2 gallons of\nwater. Boil and iUb. WiMI cool\npour over meat in tub. The brine\nshould cover the meat. Let stand\nin brine four or five weeks, turn\ning meat once a week to be sure it\nis curing liacon will cure\nin tbree weeks. Remove from tho\nbrine and smoke.\n\u201cLeaf\u201d lard may be bought in\nany butcher shop or market and\ntried out at home. Cut fat in\nliill phew. i*ut into n Initial*\ntie with just enough water to\nrover the bottom of the kettle.\nThis prevents scorching when fat\nis first put over the fire. Cook\nslowly, stirring frequently until\nthe pieces of fat are crinp and\ncrarkly. When these \"crackllns\u201d\nsettle to the bottom of the kettle\nthe lard is done. Remove from the\ntire and straiu into a sterilized\nstone jar or crock. When cold,\ntie a clean cloth and several thick*\ndesses of paper over the top..\nIs it any wonder there was a\n$025,000 deficit in llie state high\nway fund?\u201d\nGovernor Phillips has been a\nhard-boiled economist and has\nmr.de good his pledge to the people j\nin his direction of those slate in\nstitutions under his control. He\nwill be as faithful and as effective\nif given a chance with the state\nhighway department.\nSecond Annual\nGood Will lour\nWill: Airplanes l\nCoast City Takes Nincty-\nSe*en Persons in Thir\nty-Two Ships\nFRESNO. Oct. 31 -Thirty\ntwe planes carrying 97 perrons par\nticipating in the second annual good,\nwill- i,ir tour of the Los Angeles\nJunior Chamber of Commerce\nreached Fresno at noon, remained I\nlor mm h and Aook off on tluSr\nsouthward Journey that will include\nstops at Yuma. Aria., Bakersfield,\nand El Centro before they return\nhome.\nArthur Goebel, winner of the\nDole flight to the Hawaiian islands,-\npiloted the first ship that landed\nhere. The party included three j\nwomen. Mrs. Dan Emmett, wife of\nA-aemblyman Emmett of Santa j\nPaula, Miss Edith Bond of Santa\nPaula, and Miss Helen Souder, of\nHollywood. Mayor Z. S. Leymell\nheaded a reception committee that;\ngreeted the fliers.\nFloor polLher or vacuum cleaner\nfor rent $1 per day. Liquid Veneer,\nO'Oedar, Cactus. Johnson's and\nTexaco polishes and waxes. Pastcn-\nArthur Hardware Co.\u2014Advt.\nSt. Clair circulator; give you\nfurnace heat at a reasonable cost.\nLet us show you these beautifully\nfinished stoves. Douglas Hardware\nCo. \u2014Advt.\nFor the best PAINTERS and the\nBEST PAINT call the DOUGLAS\nPLANING MILL. Phone 512.\u2014Advt.\nDon\u2019t wait for thewe cold days,\nget your stove or circulator now.\nPrices very low, also stove pipe, coal\nhods and stove boards. Poston-\nArthur Hardware Co.\u2014Advt.\nTIRED AND ALL\nOUT OF SORTS\nArkansas Man Tells of the\nGood He Gets From Taking\nBlack-Draught.\nMena, Ark. \u2014\u201cIf there is a bet\nter laxative medicine made than\nThedford\u2019s Black-Draught, I've\nnever found it, and I tried a good\nmany before I began taking Black-\nDraught about twenty years ago,\u201d\nwrites Mr. H. P. Miller, who lives\non Eleventh Street, this city.\n\u201cI am satisfied with Blade-\nDraught. When I feel all out of\nsort*, my feet seem to feel heavy,\nand I feel tired when I haven\u2019t\nworked; and I get a bad, slimy\ntaste in my mouth, I just take two\nor three doses of Black-Draught\nand I feel better.\n\"I have found it good for lndi\ngestton. in fact for about every\nthing it is recommended for. We\njust keep it in the house and use\nit for biliousness, headache and\nsuch complaints. I recommend\nBlack-Draught to others.\u2019\u2019\nThis well-known medicine has\nbeen in use nearly 100 years, and\nIts popularity is constantly In\ncreasing, as growing sales clearly\nprove.\nGet the genuine\u2014see that the\nyellow package bears the name\n\u2014XlNdfQ\u00dftfe* i'rtcc 25*. Ml\nPair of Derbies\nGels Alien!inn.\nThere s a Reason\nJohn Up illy and Son James\nParade Linder New Lids\nAt Railway Station\n7 here was one proud boy in\nDouglas yesterday for a brief atop.\nU was James Reilly, son ol Mr.\n;\u2018-d Mrs. John i. Reilly, of Tucson.\ns was (ii his way home from\nChicago where, with his mother, he\ni o -n io visit uncles and aunts\nand other relatives. Such a trip\nt tnou h to make a child proud,\nb\u2019-u James had other reasons. His\n!-y 1-- v? was the biggest reason\u2014\ntad a apk nM, new\ndetby hat specially made for him\nLy li r uii\u201dl.\u2019. Chrutcph r O'Leary,\nf l Chicago. James' uncles arc hat\nh s of long experience ata an\nO'j\u00abar\\-mad\u2019 hat carries its own\nguarantee. And to have a thor\noughbred of the house of O\u2019Leary\non the underside of the hat. as is\ntfic case with James Reilly\u2014well.\nv s anotner guuranlc\nMr. O'Reilly is one of A\u201ciZona\u2019s\nhading undertakers, having b:cn\nengaged in Uie business at Tucson\nfor many fears. In years of service\nhe is o\u2019dcst in Arizona. He has a\ncustom cf always wearing a black\nderby. Jt has become a sort of\ntrade mark with him. And nov/\nthis \u201cchip off the old black,\u201d James\nReilly, is starting a custom just like\nd\u00abd's. Only James wears a better\n\u2022\u2019l'\"by, for this is custom made by\nUncle Christopher O\u2019Leary, of Chi\nci\u2022 Yesterday, wtan Mr. Reilly\ncame to meet his wife and son at\nDouglas and travel back with them,\nlie telephoned his long time friend.\nE. C. Pcrtcr, of the local firm oi\nPorter and Ames, and Mr. Porter\nmet him at the station. There is\na friendship of long years existing\nbetween them as Mr. Porter was\nemployed by Mr. Reilly for a time\nwii: a ho first came to Arizona from\nColorado In 1913.\nAs Mr. Reilly, his son. James, and\nKfr. Porta tndkfld about the sta\ntion platform waiting lor the de-\nP \u2019i;u\u201ce of the train to Tucson, the\ntwo black derbies worn by the\nRcillys attracted not a little atten\ntion from ethers about the station.\nIt was not hard to decide, however,\nwhich was the proudest of his sky\npioco. That honor went to James\nReilly.\nMr. Reilly also visited Mr. and\nSmith\u2019s Grocery\nPhones 784-785 SATURDAY AND MONDAY 1950 A Amiue\nPotatoes\nIdaho's\n10 lbs 29c\nLemons\nLarge Size\nDo/. 23c\nFresh Tomatoes\nLocal, Ripe\nPound 5c\nSnowdrift\nSaturday Only\n3 pounds 59c\nCoffee\nFolger's\nLb...43c 2 1b5..35c\nApples\nWashington Jonathons\n80x..51.90 Lb...5c\nPancake Flour\nAunt Jemima\nSmall pkg. 13c\nLarge, each 35c\nCorn Meal\n9-lb. Sacks\nEach 41c\nCinger Snaps\nH-lb pkgs 20c\n--elect tho best\n\\w. w v candidates'\nx Your ballot\n\\is needed/\nv\nMrs. F. O. Mack ay while in the city,\nthere bcin:> a long time friendship\nfcetween thrm. He talked of busi\nness and declared that Tucson, like\nothc\" parts cf Arizona, has been\nfaring better than most parts of\nthe country. \u201cMost any part of\nArizona is n coed place to live,\u201d\nr-aid lie. \"Wc think Tucson is the\nbest spot in the slate, but all ol\nArizona i:- good, place to call home.\nBuriness, it is true, has not been as\nbri k in recent weeks in general\nlines as the rule for the season, but\nthe m ntal state is worse, I think,\nthan the a dual condition.\nIn my hnc of business, that of\nan undertaker, we a-e not given to\nadvertising, and p-rhaps it is best\nthat way. It so happens that wc\nhave been busier lhan usual in the\nlast week or so. But our business\nis not subject to stimulation through\nadvertising. Wc try to meet the\nsituations as they arise and render\nthe best possible service for, as you\nknow, our p r csencc is demanded in\nthe hour of misfortune for others.\n\u201cI've know'll Ed Porter for many\nyears and it was a pleasure to gef\nan opportunity to come to Douglas\nfor a brief visit with him and your\nother good citizens, Mr. and Mrs. F.\nO. Mackey. I have a tot of good\nfrirnd;' in Douglas and I like the\ncity. Douglas and Tucson, have a\nnumber of things in which they\nought to share a mutual interest\np.nd. finally, progress for all of our\ncities in Arizona must come from\nmutual endeavor, because anything\nwhich damages one, does an injury\nto the rest of them.\u201d\nMr. and M\u00bbs. Reilly and son,\nJames, went west on the afternoon\ntrain for Tucson, where Jamas will\nparade his new hat to the boys and j\ngirls at home.\n\n\u201cNo Breakfast Complete Without\nThe Du nat ch\"\nBarbecue Meat\nSERVED EVERY DAY\nSUNDAY INCLUDED\nPEYTON\u2019S BABY BEEF\nBeef Round Steaks, lb 38c\nBeef Loin Steaks, lb 38c\nBeef T-Bone Steaks, lb 38c\nBeef Prime Rib Roast, lb 27c\nBeet Cbtick Roast, lb 25c\nBeef Rib Stew, lb 20c\nBeef Liver, lb 25c\nVeal Round Steak, lb 38c\nVeal Loin Steak, lb .3Bc\nVeal Chops, lb 38c\nVeal Chuck Roast, lb 20c\nCalf Liver, lb 40c\nPork Loin Chops, lb 35c\nPork SKouMer Shank End, lb 25c\nPork Shoulder, Large End, 1b...... 28c\nPork Ham Roast, lb. 33c\nPork Spare Ribs, lb 30c\nPork Sausage, lb 25c\nSPECIAL HOUR SALE\n7 to 9 A. M. 1 to 3 P. M.\nMust Call In Person\nVeal Round Steak, lb 25c\nVeal Loin Steak and Chops, lb. 22V2C\nVeal Chuck Roast, lb 18c\nVeal Shoulder Roast, lb 20c\nCalf Liver, lb 30c\nBlack Hawk Hams\nSKINNED\u2014 or\nBy Whole or Half, pound \u00abDC\nBrick Chile Con Carne, each 27c\nRath\u2019s Bacon, lb 33c\nBoneless Ham Butts, lb 38c\nSalt Pork, every day, lb 25c\nLong Horn Cheese, lb 30c\nHens, White, alive, lb., 26c;\ndressed, lb 30c\nMeat Pies, home made, Veal,\n20c; Pork 20c\nNucoa, Saturday only, 2 lbs 45c\nEggs, Saturday only, guaranteed\nfresh, 3 dozen $1.35\nOates Gives S4OO\nCash Bond And Is\nGiven His Freedom\nRay G. Oates, arrested on Wed\nnvjsday by customs officers charged\nwith having narcotics upon his per\nson when he attempted to enter the\nUnited State; from Mexico, was\nbrought before U. S. Commissioner\nH. C. Beumler yesterday on a com\nplaint sworn to by Deputy U. S.\nCustoms Collector E. M. Specht in\ncharge of the Douglas port. After\na hearing, in which Oates was rep\nresented by W. O. Gilmore, the\nbond was fixed at S4OO and Oates\ndeposited the sum in cash and was\nreleased.\nOates had $672.40 on his person\nwhen he wr\u2022> taken into custody. He\nalso had 10 grains of gum opium.\nIt is alleged. He told the officers\nw'ho arrested him that he once had\nbeen a user of the drug but that\nhe w'as not now using it. Just why\nhe had it with him he did not ex\nplain.\nTHE MAN WITH THE\n\u2018\u2018HAIR-TRIGGER\" TEMPER\nHe was irritable at the office,\nand grouchy at home. Hia\nenemies increased, his friends\nbecame fewer. Then one day\nhis doctor told him the truth.\nHe had been handicapped by\nconstipation for years. It had\nbrought headaches and con\nstantly irritating ills to make\nhim \u201ctouchy.\u201d It had stolen\nhis energy and good nature.\nHis doctor suggested eating\nKellogg\u2019s All-Bran regularly.\nAnd in a few days he was a\nchanged man, cheery, ambi\ntious and on the road to suc\ncess and happiness.\nConstipation is so unneces\nsary it can be overcome by\neating delicious Kellogg\u2019s All-\nBran. This delightful, ready\nto-eat cereal has been improved\nin both texture and taste.\nTwo tablespoonfuls of\nBoynton Makes\nw\nForced Landing\nOn Flight West\nWINSLOW. Ariz.. Oct. 31.\nStanley Boynton, youthful eastern\nflier seeking to set a junior trans\ncontinental flight record, landed\nhere at 12:45 p. m. <M. S. T.) from\nThoreau, N. M. He took off from\nGuymon, Okla., this morning.\nIn a forced landing 30 miles 'east\nof Thoreau Boynton broke the tail\nwheel of his plane. He announced\nhe would remain in Winslow -to\nnight, leaving early tomorrow for\nLos Angeles with a stop at King\nman, Ariz.\nYoung Boynton had planned -to\nstop in Phoenix tonight but got off\nhis course and decided to go direct\ni to Los Angeles. His elapsed time\nfrom Guymon to Winslow was 4:10.\n1\nKellogg's All-Bran daily are\nguaranteed to prevent and re\nlieve both temporary and re*-\nearring constipation. Use tide\nnatural method and avoid the\ndangers of habit-fanning pills\nand drugs.\nServe All-Bran with mfllc\nor cream, with fruits or honey\nadded. Use in cooking too. Sold\nby all grocers in the familiar\nred-and-green package. Made\nby Kellogg in Battle Creek,\nAll-Bran\nImproved in Toxtmro mnd Taoto_\nPears\nNo. 2fi Cans, Del Monte\nEach 32c\nSpaghetti\nVan Camp\u2019s, Med. Cans\n2 cans 23c\nI\nCelery\nLarge Stalk, Well Bleached\nEach 12c\nj\nGrapefruit\nArizona Seedless, 4 for 25c\nWith Seeds\nEach 5c J\n\u2014.l i a, ii.\u25a0 i\nLux 1\nw\nFor Woolens and Silks\nSmall Size\nEach 10c\nTomato Sonp\nCampbell\u2019s\n3 cans 29c\nDromedary Dates.\n10-oz. pkgs.\nEach 19e\nPeaches\nDel Monte, No. 1 Tall Cans\n2 for 25c\nBrown Sugar\nPowdered\n3 pkgs.. 28c\nTHREE","height":"26481","width":"20595"}}
